25|$|After the 28 Democratic {{senators}} {{walked out}} of the Senate chamber, Secretary of the Senate Angelo Aponte turned off the lights in the Senate chamber and stopped the TV broadcast of the Senate session. Nevertheless, the remaining senators proceeded to vote for new leadership, removing Democratic Senator Malcolm Smith from his position <b>as</b> <b>Majority</b> <b>Leader</b> and Temporary President of the Senate, and replacing him with two people: Republican Minority Leader Dean Skelos <b>as</b> <b>Majority</b> <b>Leader,</b> and Pedro Espada as Temporary President. Historically, the majority leadership and the temporary presidency of the Senate were held by the same person. However, in the new arrangement, Espada was to be the Temporary President of the Senate, while Skelos would become Majority Leader.|$|E
